# Maison Parfum Design System

Define the visual language for all UI work. Every component, page, and section should feel like a luxury fragrance house — calm, editorial, and intentional.

## Brand Style

Maison Parfum is a luxury fragrance house with an editorial aesthetic and premium minimalism.

Design inspiration:

- Byredo
- Le Labo
- Diptyque
- Maison Francis Kurkdjian

Guidelines:

- Prioritize restraint over decoration
- Let product imagery and typography carry the experience
- Favor quiet confidence over loud branding
- Every layout should feel curated, not crowded

## Typography

- Use serif headings (`--font-heading` / Playfair Display)
- Use sans-serif body text (`--font-body` / Inter)
- Establish clear hierarchy: eyebrow → title → body → caption
- Editorial titles should be large and confident (`text-3xl` to `text-7xl` at appropriate breakpoints)
- Use generous line heights for body copy (`leading-relaxed` or looser)
- Eyebrow labels: uppercase, wide tracking, small size, muted color
- Avoid mixing too many font sizes on a single screen

## Spacing

- Prefer whitespace over density
- Use large section padding (`py-12` to `py-32` depending on context)
- Keep content within comfortable reading width (`max-w-xl` to `max-w-3xl` for prose)
- Use consistent grid gaps (`gap-8` to `gap-12`)
- Let sections breathe — never pack elements tightly without reason
- Align with `Container` for horizontal rhythm

## Colors

Use the existing CSS variable palette:

- `--background` — warm ivory (`#f8f5f0`)
- `--foreground` — high contrast text (`#111111`)
- `--primary` — refined gold accent (`#c9a45c`)
- `--secondary` — deep neutral (`#1a1a1a`)
- `--muted` — soft section backgrounds (`#e9e4dc`)
- `--border` — subtle dividers (`#d9d3ca`)

Guidelines:

- Neutral palette first; gold accent sparingly
- Warm ivory backgrounds, not pure white pages
- Soft borders instead of heavy outlines
- High contrast text for readability
- Muted grays only for secondary information
- Avoid bright, saturated, or playful color combinations

## Components

- Refined and understated
- Avoid flashy UI patterns (gradients, glows, badges, loud CTAs)
- Avoid excessive shadows — prefer borders and spacing for depth
- Border radius should remain subtle (`rounded-xl` for controls, `rounded-3xl` for cards)
- Cards: light borders, white or ivory surfaces, minimal chrome
- Buttons: simple shapes, restrained hover states (opacity or color shift, not scale)
- Forms: clean inputs with soft borders and subtle focus rings
- Icons: thin strokes, used sparingly

## Interactions

- Smooth, understated transitions (`transition-all`, 200–300ms)
- Luxury feel: deliberate, never snappy or playful
- No aggressive animations (no bounce, shake, or exaggerated scale)
- Hover effects should be subtle (opacity, border color, slight image scale at most)
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` when adding animation
- Focus states must be visible but elegant

## Do Not

- Do not use inline styles
- Do not introduce colors outside the design tokens without reason
- Do not add drop shadows for decoration
- Do not use dense, marketplace-style layouts
- Do not over-animate hover states or page transitions
